    public static let infoPage2 = "Data privacy is a natural concern for location sharing apps.  CrossedPaths prioritizes data privacy employing multiple strategies:\n\n1. All data is stored locally on your phone. No one, not even other apps on your phone, can access it. Sharing data with any group administrator is voluntary.  It is your responsibility to read the privacy policy of that group which is provided everytime when you send data.\n\n2. You have complete control over when to collect data. Data is automatically deleted after a week. You can delete all data at any time.\n\n3. The digital signature of your location history instead of your actual location history is stored locally on your phone. These signatures cannot be traced back to origin location and time and can only be compared to on another to check if they match.\n\n4. Decentralized model lets your phone download the database and compare on the phone. No one else knows your overlap results.\n\n5. Only digital signatures of timestamped locations that fit the group adminstrator's description are sent to that administrator.  We require the administrator clearly specify the specific locations and times that they collect in their privacy policy.  Through programming, we implement these exact descriptions\n\n6. If you still have reservations on data privacy, a path you can take is to start updating location only when you anticipate meeting group members that do not live with you, such as going to work or out shopping. At other times, you can turn off the location updates.\n\n7. You are not allowed to share your digital signatures collected following one group's description to another group, so you will not accidentally share data to the wrong group.\n\n8. In rare occasions, we or a third party working with us may ask you to voluntarily share all your digital signatures in the past 7 days.  More privacy protocols will be communicated to you at that time. A password will be provided to enable you to share those infomration if you choose."
